{"id":"1509.02886","submitter":"Azeef Muhammed P A","authors":"Azeef Muhammed P A and A R Rajan","title":"Cross-connections of completely simple semigroups","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1142/S1793557116500534","report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A completely simple semigroup S is a semigroup without zero which has no\nproper ideals and contains a primitive idempotent. It is known that S is a\nregular semigroup and any completely simple semigroup is isomorphic to the Rees\nmatrix semigroup. In the study of structure theory of regular semigroups,\nK.S.S. Nambooripad introduced the concept of normal categories to construct the\nsemigroup from its principal left(right) ideals using cross-connections. A\nnormal category C is a small category with subobjects wherein each object of\nthe category has an associated idempotent normal cone and each morphism admits\na normal factorization. A cross-connection between two normal categories C and\nD is a local isomorphism frm D to N*C where N*C is the normal dual of the\ncategory C. In this paper, we identify the normal categories associated with a\ncompletely simple semigroup S and show that the semigroup of normal cones TL(S)\nis isomorphic to a semi-direct product of semigroups. We characterize the\ncross-connections in this case and show that each sandwich matrix P correspond\nto a cross-connection. Further we use each of these cross-connections to give a\nrepresentation of the completely simple semigroup as a cross-connection\nsemigroup.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Sep 2015 18:53:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-24"}
